Well-log Dataset from Numerical Bayesian Methods Applied to Signal Processing

Source: R/fastcpd-data.R
well_log.Rd

This is the well-known well-log dataset used in many changepoint papers obtained from Alan Turing Institute GitHub repository and licensed under the MIT license. Outliers with value less or equal to 1e5 are removed.

Usage

well_log

Format

A Time-Series of length 3989.

Source

<https://github.com/alan-turing-institute/TCPD>

Examples

# \donttest{
result <- fastcpd.mean(
  well_log, beta = (1 + 1) * log(length(well_log)) / 2 * 2,  trim = 0.002
)
summary(result)
#> 
#> Call:
#> fastcpd.mean(data = well_log, beta = (1 + 1) * log(length(well_log))/2 * 
#>     2, trim = 0.002)
#> 
#> Change points:
#> 10 566 704 776 1021 1057 1198 1347 1406 1502 1661 1842 2023 2385 2445 2507 2567 2744 3709 3820 3976 
#> 
#> Cost values:
#> 217.3729 5150.785 1263.459 669.6558 2243.166 334.5351 1304.398 1401.215 563.1558 898.8624 1469.775 1677.183 1672.662 3321.132 545.3822 568.6718 541.6102 1625.089 8970.966 1018.747 1462.606 122.1578 
plot(result)

# }
